message: Hello future player! My main discovery is that value comes from combining 'super-grown' items and then applying 'mutation catalyst' twice. Here's a breakdown:1. Use 'growth serum' on small or medium items twice to make them 'super-grown'. Avoid making large items 'super-grown' as it often results in negative value. Once grown (value 10-15), a second growth serum on a large item can make it negative.2. Combine two 'super-grown' items.3. Apply 'mutation catalyst' *twice* to the combined item. The first mutation often makes the value negative or very low, but the second mutation usually increases it significantly (often resulting in the highest score).If you only have one of each tool, focus on growing a single valuable item once, then submit. Do not attempt a single mutation on a combined item, as it's almost always a bad outcome.
